<p>
<p>What is meant with the ANCOVA assumption <em>homogeneity of regression slopes</em>?</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
<penalty>0</penalty>
<defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
<shuffleanswers>false</shuffleanswers>
<single>true</single>
<answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
The variance of Y is equal for all levels of the covariate X.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Both variable Y and covariate X are normally distributed.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
The mean value of Y is equal for all groups across all levels of covariate X.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="100" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
The relationship between variable Y and covariate X is equal for all groups.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Correct
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
